itemDescription: British politician and Member of Parliament (1943-2012)

wikipedia_page.main: John Cradock Maples, Baron Maples (22 April 1943 – 9 June 2012) was a British Conservative politician who served as Member of Parliament (MP) for Lewisham West from 1983 to 1992 and Stratford-upon-Avon from 1997 to 2010. He was made a life peer in 2010.
